ctory. There's no reliance on Docker, environment variables, system properties, or external services. I might include agent guidance mentioning no environment or system properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is required: jetty-webapp brings its needed Jetty and Servlet API dependencies transitively, and meaningful coverage is reachable with an embedded Jetty Server/WebAppContext using a temporary local webapp directory.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are needed. Generated tests can create a temporary webapp directory with WEB-INF/web.xml/static files, configure WebAppContext.setWar(...), attach it to an embedded Server with an ephemeral port, and exercise descriptor/classloader behavior locally.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that choose optional Jetty features such as JMX, JSP, annotation scanning, JNDI, or plus configuration may require additional Jetty modules, but those are not necessary for core jetty-webapp coverage.\",\n    \"The javac failure is due to an API change in WebAppClassLoader.Context in 9.4.0.RC1, not missing setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_070df11da57cbc1a016a42755d1fdc8197ac859a9f3e782378\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 694, "output": 736, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30614, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782740304791, "responseId": "resp_070df11da57cbc1a016a42755141dc8197b2401d7e795e5189"}, "toolResults": []}
